   <h1><span>The Norwegian Food Safety Authority</span></h1>
 </div>
 <div class="documentBody">
   <p><strong>The Norwegian Food Safety Authority</strong>, with its head office<b> </b>in Oslo, is a joint subordinate agency under the Ministry of Agriculture and Food, the Ministry of Health and Care Services and The Ministry of Fisheries and Coastal Affairs. The Norwegian Food Safety Authority has 8 regional and 64 local offices, and supervises the safety and quality of seafood. The National Fish and Seafood Centre is located in Bergen.</p>
